	<item>
		<type>Multiple Choice</type>
		   <label>Which statement describes best why you should document assumptions?</label>
			<choice>
				<choicelabel>Assumptions might prove to be wrong. Knowing which assumptions were incorrect allows baseline adjustments in case of project crisis.</choicelabel>
				<credit></credit>
				<elements>radio</elements>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<choicelabel>Assumption analysis is a valuable tool and technique to explore the validity of assumptions during risk identification.</choicelabel>
				<credit>2</credit>
				<elements>radio</elements>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<choicelabel>Assumptions limit the project management team&#39;s options for decision making because they can not be controlled by the team.</choicelabel>
				<credit></credit>
				<elements>radio</elements>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<choicelabel>In case of schedule or budget overruns, the documentation of assumptions supports a clear assignment of responsibility.</choicelabel>
				<credit></credit>
				<elements>radio</elements>
			</choice>
	</item>
